{
 "cells": [

   "id": "2fe6f1ca",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# `random_spheres`\n",
    "Generates randomly located, non-overlapping spheres using the 'random sequential addition' technique. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "ca6690a7",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2022-04-25T01:54:07.310878Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2022-04-25T01:54:07.310104Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2022-04-25T01:54:09.572133Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2022-04-25T01:54:09.571560Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import porespy as ps\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "ps.visualization.set_mpl_style()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "c2fb3423",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## `im` or `shape`\n",
    "The function can either add spheres an existing image, or create a new image of the given shape and add spheres to that.  Let's start with an empty image, and set the void fraction to a low value:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "a82ba7b0",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2022-04-25T01:54:09.582136Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2022-04-25T01:54:09.581937Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2022-04-25T01:54:09.970757Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2022-04-25T01:54:09.970339Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 400x400 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "image/png": {
       "height": 383,
       "width": 383
      }
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "shape = [300, 300]\n",
    "r = 15\n",
    "im = ps.generators.random_spheres(shape=shape, r=r)\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 1, figsize=[4, 4])\n",
    "ax.axis(False)\n",
    "ax.imshow(im, origin='lower', interpolation='none');"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "7aa1f797",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Now let's fill up the remaining space with as many smaller spheres as possible:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "b23dc537",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2022-04-25T01:54:09.973785Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2022-04-25T01:54:09.973565Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2022-04-25T01:54:10.023529Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2022-04-25T01:54:10.023047Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 400x400 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "image/png": {
       "height": 383,
       "width": 383
      }
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "r = 5\n",
    "im = ps.generators.random_spheres(im=im, r=r)\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 1, figsize=[4, 4])\n",
    "ax.axis(False)\n",
    "ax.imshow(im, origin='lower', interpolation='none');"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "c96de124",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## `edges`\n",
    "Spheres can either be fully contained within the image or be truncated at the edges:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "d19cbadd",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2022-04-25T01:54:10.026472Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2022-04-25T01:54:10.026265Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2022-04-25T01:54:10.128545Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2022-04-25T01:54:10.128058Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 800x400 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "image/png": {
       "height": 384,
       "width": 745
      }
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=[8, 4])\n",
    "\n",
    "r = 20\n",
    "mode = 'contained'\n",
    "im1 = ps.generators.random_spheres(shape=shape, r=r, edges=mode)\n",
    "ax[0].imshow(im1, origin='lower', interpolation='none')\n",
    "ax[0].axis(False)\n",
    "ax[0].set_title(f'edges = {mode}')\n",
    "\n",
    "mode = 'extended'\n",
    "im2 = ps.generators.random_spheres(shape=shape, r=r, edges=mode)\n",
    "ax[1].imshow(im2, origin='lower', interpolation='none')\n",
    "ax[1].axis(False)\n",
    "ax[1].set_title(f'edges = {mode}');"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f1da79f5",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## `clearance`\n",
    "Spheres can be made to partially overlap, the so called 'cherry pit' model, or to have some clearance:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "ccc9dd80",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2022-04-25T01:54:10.131451Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2022-04-25T01:54:10.131232Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2022-04-25T01:54:10.227236Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2022-04-25T01:54:10.226683Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 800x400 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "image/png": {
       "height": 384,
       "width": 745
      }
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=[8, 4])\n",
    "\n",
    "c = -4\n",
    "im1 = ps.generators.random_spheres(shape=shape, r=r, clearance=c)\n",
    "ax[0].imshow(im1, origin='lower', interpolation='none')\n",
    "ax[0].axis(False)\n",
    "ax[0].set_title(f'clearance = {c}')\n",
    "\n",
    "c = 4\n",
    "im2 = ps.generators.random_spheres(shape=shape, r=r, clearance=c)\n",
    "ax[1].imshow(im2, origin='lower', interpolation='none')\n",
    "ax[1].axis(False)\n",
    "ax[1].set_title(f'clearance = {c}');"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f04795f4",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## `protrusion`\n",
    "\n",
    "This controls how much the added spheres are allowed to protrude into the background. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "id": "a0043656",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1000x400 with 3 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "image/png": {
       "height": 313,
       "width": 984
      }
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "im1 = ps.generators.blobs(shape=[300, 300], porosity=0.5)\n",
    "im2 = ps.generators.random_spheres(im=im1, r=8, protrusion=-5)\n",
    "im3 = ps.generators.random_spheres(im=im1, r=8, protrusion=5)\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=[10, 4])\n",
    "ax[0].imshow(im1, origin='lower', interpolation='none')\n",
    "ax[1].imshow(im2, origin='lower', interpolation='none')\n",
    "ax[2].imshow(im3, origin='lower', interpolation='none');"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "9a97428d",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "In the case of pre-existing spheres this can be used to give some clearance between existing spheres and new ones by using a negative value:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "id": "49de3848",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2022-04-25T01:54:10.230265Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2022-04-25T01:54:10.230053Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2022-04-25T01:54:10.461393Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2022-04-25T01:54:10.460914Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1000x400 with 3 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "image/png": {
       "height": 313,
       "width": 984
      }
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "im1 = np.zeros([300, 300])\n",
    "im2 = ps.generators.random_spheres(im=im1, r=15, clearance=5)\n",
    "im3 = ps.generators.random_spheres(im=im2, r=5, protrusion=-5)\n",
    "im4 = ps.generators.random_spheres(im=im2, r=5, protrusion=5)\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=[10, 4])\n",
    "ax[0].imshow(im2, origin='lower', interpolation='none')\n",
    "ax[1].imshow(im3, origin='lower', interpolation='none')\n",
    "ax[2].imshow(im4, origin='lower', interpolation='none');"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "3eaac69f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## `phi` and `maxiter`\n",
    "\n",
    "The number of spheres to add can be controlled directly by specifying `maxiter`, or implicitly by specifying `phi` (the solid volume fraction).  Setting `phi` will attempt to compute the correct value of `maxiter` internally so will not give the exact `phi` requested:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "id": "42621cee",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2022-04-25T01:54:10.464637Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2022-04-25T01:54:10.464372Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2022-04-25T01:54:10.607572Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2022-04-25T01:54:10.606870Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 800x400 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "image/png": {
       "height": 384,
       "width": 745
      }
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=[8, 4])\n",
    "\n",
    "maxiter = 5\n",
    "im1 = ps.generators.random_spheres(shape=shape, r=r, clearance=c, maxiter=maxiter)\n",
    "ax[0].imshow(im1, origin='lower', interpolation='none')\n",
    "ax[0].axis(False)\n",
    "ax[0].set_title(f'maxiter = {maxiter}')\n",
    "\n",
    "vf = 0.2\n",
    "im2 = ps.generators.random_spheres(shape=shape, r=r, clearance=c, phi=vf)\n",
    "ax[1].axis(False)\n",
    "ax[1].set_title(f'phi = {vf}')\n",
    "ax[1].imshow(im2, origin='lower', interpolation='none');"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "0564b6e1",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## `smooth`\n",
    "\n",
    "Controls whether or not the inserted spheres have the little nibs or pips on each face.  Note that if `smooth=True`, then `r` is increased by 1 to ensure the radius of the inserted spheres matches the requested value."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "id": "a2366c78",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 800x400 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "image/png": {
       "height": 384,
       "width": 745
      }
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=[8, 4])\n",
    "\n",
    "smooth = True\n",
    "im1 = ps.generators.random_spheres(shape=[100, 100], r=10, smooth=smooth)\n",
    "ax[0].imshow(im1, origin='lower', interpolation='none')\n",
    "ax[0].axis(False)\n",
    "ax[0].set_title(f'smooth = {smooth}')\n",
    "\n",
    "smooth = False\n",
    "im2 = ps.generators.random_spheres(shape=[100, 100], r=10, smooth=smooth)\n",
    "ax[1].axis(False)\n",
    "ax[1].set_title(f'smooth = {smooth}')\n",
    "ax[1].imshow(im2, origin='lower', interpolation='none');"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b03cf17e",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## `seed`\n",
    "\n",
    "This function uses `numba` to accelerate the insertion process, which means that the `numpy` random number generator is *not* used.  To generate a repeatable realization of the spheres, pass an integer value to the `seed` argument:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "id": "ef0e9264",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1200x400 with 3 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "image/png": {
       "height": 383,
       "width": 1140
      }
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=[12, 4])\n",
    "\n",
    "seed = 1\n",
    "im1 = ps.generators.random_spheres(shape=[100, 100], r=10, seed=seed)\n",
    "ax[0].imshow(im1, origin='lower', interpolation='none')\n",
    "ax[0].axis(False)\n",
    "ax[0].set_title(f'seed = {seed}')\n",
    "\n",
    "seed = 1\n",
    "im2 = ps.generators.random_spheres(shape=[100, 100], r=10, seed=seed)\n",
    "ax[1].axis(False)\n",
    "ax[1].set_title(f'seed = {seed}')\n",
    "ax[1].imshow(im2, origin='lower', interpolation='none')\n",
    "\n",
    "seed = 2\n",
    "im2 = ps.generators.random_spheres(shape=[100, 100], r=10, seed=seed)\n",
    "ax[2].axis(False)\n",
    "ax[2].set_title(f'seed = {seed}')\n",
    "ax[2].imshow(im2, origin='lower', interpolation='none');"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b265f3d2",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## `value`\n",
    "\n",
    "The default behavior is to insert spheres with values of `0` or `False`, but this can be specified using the `value` argument.  This is useful when inserting several different sizes of spheres sequentially:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "id": "6a694c39",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 800x400 with 4 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "image/png": {
       "height": 383,
       "width": 782
      }
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=[8, 4])\n",
    "\n",
    "value = 2\n",
    "im1 = ps.generators.random_spheres(shape=[100, 100], r=10, value=value)\n",
    "im1 = ps.generators.random_spheres(im=im1, r=5, value=value+2, protrusion=-2)\n",
    "h = ax[0].imshow(im1, origin='lower', interpolation='none')\n",
    "ax[0].axis(False)\n",
    "ax[0].set_title(f'value = {value} and {value + 2}')\n",
    "fig.colorbar(h)\n",
    "\n",
    "value = -2\n",
    "im2 = ps.generators.random_spheres(shape=[100, 100], r=10, value=value)\n",
    "im2 = ps.generators.random_spheres(im=im2, r=5, value=value-2, protrusion=-2)\n",
    "h = ax[1].imshow(im2, origin='lower', interpolation='none')\n",
    "ax[1].axis(False)\n",
    "ax[1].set_title(f'value = {value} and {value - 2}')\n",
    "fig.colorbar(h);"
   ]
  }
 ],
